org.efaps.util

Class EFapsException

  • java.lang.Object
    • java.lang.Throwable
      • java.lang.Exception
        • org.efaps.util.EFapsException
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Serializable
    Direct Known Subclasses:
    CacheReloadException

    public class EFapsException
extends Exception
    The class is the exception class used to throw exception. This exceptions are shown in the user interface (web browser). The exception text stands in the properties. The key value in the property is the name of the class (className) plus the id (id) plus the strings .Id, .Error and .Action to show the user a internationalized description of the exception.
